reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Get your own wall anchors or toggle bolts
reviews.reviewText: Assembly was pretty straightforward though it did take a while. Parts fit together well and instructions were Ikea-like. Only problem I had was that the wall anchors and screws provided to mount the unit on the wall were flimsy and broke during installation. I picked up 1/4" x 3" wall anchors at HomeDepot, drilled out the holes in the unit, and the unit was securely installed. I was impressed at how sturdy the assembled unit was.

reviews.reviewText: Night stand was easy enough to assemble. Looks cute; however, it’s not the best quality. Equivalent to ikea. It was already fading around the edges when it arrived.

reviews.reviewText: The nightstand arrived with missing parts so I contacted the seller. There was a lot of back and forth and it took a couple of weeks, but they sent a complete replacement. It is not a high quality nightstand, but it is very nice looking. I appreciate the help that I was provided even though it took awhile to get it figured out.

reviews.reviewText: I think this should be worth 20 to $25. The finish is very easy to scratch and take the polish off of by rubbing with a microfiber wet cloth to clean it so be careful. The drawer does not have any support so just hangs loose but there is a catch at the end to prevent it from coming all the way out. Not sure if I'll hang this up. Will probably get something else.Instructions are very busy looking but it is very repetitive once you begin. It says it takes 15 minutes but it took me 35 minutes to assemble. FYI items labeled Number one and two are switched with each other.
